¶ Just sit right back
    and you'll hear a tale ¶

00:06.307 --> 00:08.340
¶ A tale of a fateful trip ¶

00:08.409 --> 00:10.843
¶ That started
    from this tropic port ¶

00:10.911 --> 00:12.744
¶ Aboard this tiny ship ¶

00:12.813 --> 00:15.313
¶ The mate was
     a mighty sailin' man ¶

00:15.382 --> 00:17.616
¶ The Skipper brave and sure ¶

00:17.685 --> 00:20.119
¶ Five passengers
      set sail that day ¶

00:20.187 --> 00:22.320
¶ For a three hour tour ¶

00:22.389 --> 00:25.156
¶ A three hour tour ¶

00:25.225 --> 00:27.159
[thunder rumbles]

00:27.228 --> 00:29.561
¶ The weather started
     getting rough ¶

00:29.630 --> 00:31.663
¶ The tiny ship was tossed ¶

00:31.731 --> 00:34.466
¶ If not for the courage
    of the fearless crew ¶

00:34.535 --> 00:36.334
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

00:36.403 --> 00:38.637
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

